SUMMARY:Azure Decoded: Governance in a Modern Lakehouse with Azure Databri
 cks and OneLak
DESCRIPTION:Microsoft Reactor Toronto\nIn this session\, you’ll learn ho
 w Azure Databricks\, Microsoft Fabric\, and OneLake come together to deliv
 er a unified\, modern Lakehouse architecture.\n\nWe’ll walk through how 
 data flows seamlessly between platforms\, how metadata stays consistent\, 
 and how shared governance is enforced end‑to‑end using Unity Catalog a
 nd Microsoft Purview. You’ll see how security\, lineage\, and access con
 trols extend across both ecosystems—enabling teams to operate with a sin
 gle governance framework while taking advantage of each platform’s stren
 gths.\n\n**What you’ll learn:**\n\n* How Azure Databricks\, Microsoft Fa
 bric\, and OneLake align to deliver a cohesive Lakehouse architecture.\n* 
 How unified governance works across both platforms using Unity Catalog and
  Microsoft Purview.\n* Practical patterns for integrating Databricks and F
 abric\, including cross-platform data sharing and metadata consistency.\n\
 n**Who should attend:** Developers\, solution architects\, and technical p
 rofessionals who want to prepare for DP-750 Azure Databricks Data Engineer
  certification.\n\n***\n\n[Secure Unity Catalog objects](https://learn.mic
 rosoft.com/training/wwl-databricks/secure-unity-catalog-objects/?wt.mc_id=
 meetup_26860_webpage_reactor)\n[Govern Unity Catalog objects](https://lear
 n.microsoft.com/training/wwl-databricks/govern-unity-catalog-objects/?wt.m
 c_id=meetup_26860_webpage_reactor)\n\nThis session is a part of a series! 
 Learn more **[here](https://developer.microsoft.com/reactor/series/S-1644/
 ?wt.mc_id=meetup_S-1644_webpage_reactor)**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/microsoft-reactor-toronto/events/3135
 11564/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260224T205143Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260224T205143Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
